<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8628> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8628" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 741, footnote 145" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3126> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3126" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap., Degrassi 52f., 125, 468f. ([Q. Ca]lpurnius C. [f. C. n.] Piso); Obseq. 26; Chr. 354 (Flacco et Pisone), so also Fast. Hyd., and Chr. Pasc.; Oros. 5.6.1; Cassiod.; and on Flaccus, CIL 1\n     .2.635- ILS 22; SIG(3) 688; Liv. Per. 56. Flaccus repelled an invasion of Illyria by{489} Vardaei (Liv. Per. 56; App. Illyr. 10). Piso in Hither Spain attacked Pallantia (App. Ib. 83), while Obsequens records a defeat at Numantia (26; see Schulten, Gesch. Numantia 81)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3125> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3125" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On Piso's filiation, see SIG(3) 683, line 42." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3093> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3093" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The latest possible date before his consulship. Cf. SIG\n     683, line 42.{484}" .
